What are you doing!?

253
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:16,460
Her willingness to order around a
high school student she just met

254
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:18,630
without any problems
is so very her.

255
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:22,840
If I had first met her like this,
as a junior high school student,

256
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:25,770
I probably would have thought
that she was really crazy.

257
00:12:25,770 --> 00:12:27,540
At Haruhi's direction,

258
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:30,750
I ran this way and that,
drawing white lines.

259
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:33,480
This was the mysterious message
that Taniguchi had mentioned,

260
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,970
but I never thought that I would be
the one that drew it...

261
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,250
Hmph. It's okay.

262
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:39,480
Well, excuse me.

263
00:12:43,690 --> 00:12:46,260
Do you think aliens exist?

264
00:12:46,260 --> 00:12:47,430
Well, that was sudden.

265
00:12:47,430 --> 00:12:49,660
Answer the question.

266
00:12:49,660 --> 00:12:50,930
I guess they do.

267
00:12:50,930 --> 00:12:52,300
What about time travelers?

268
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,930
Wouldn't be strange
if there were.

269
00:12:53,930 --> 00:12:55,500
And espers?

270
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,370
There are probably enough of them
to walk in formation.

271
00:12:57,370 --> 00:12:58,810
People from
other dimensions?

272
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:00,740
I haven't met any
of them yet.

273
00:13:03,110 --> 00:13:05,050
That's the uniform for North High,
isn't it?

274
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:06,110
Well, yeah.

275
00:13:06,110 --> 00:13:07,620
What's your name?

276
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:08,950
John Smith.

277
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:11,190
Are you stupid
or something?

278
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:13,820
Let's just say that I want
to stay anonymous.

279
00:13:13,820 --> 00:13:15,320
Who's the girl
you were carrying?

280
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,820
My big sister.

281
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:19,560
She had a sudden case
of narcolepsy.

282
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:21,360
She falls asleep regardless
of location,

283
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,860
so I was carrying her.

284
00:13:22,860 --> 00:13:24,170
Hmph.

285
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:26,470
So, what in the world
is this?

286
00:13:26,470 --> 00:13:29,000
Can't you tell by looking?
It's a message.

287
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,870
It's not for Orihime
or Hikoboshi, is it?

288
00:13:31,870 --> 00:13:33,540
How did you know that?

289
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:35,410
Well, it is Tanabata.

290
00:13:35,410 --> 00:13:38,510
I just remembered someone I knew
doing something similar.

291
00:13:38,510 --> 00:13:41,280
Huh. I'd love to meet
that person.

292
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,080
So, that person goes
to North High?

293
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,110
You could say that.

294
00:13:45,620 --> 00:13:47,050
North High, huh?

295
00:13:52,230 --> 00:13:54,660
I'm going home. I've accomplished
my goal, after all.

296
00:13:54,660 --> 00:13:55,830
Bye.

297
00:13:55,830 --> 00:13:58,770
And not even a thanks
for helping her.

298
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,590
Miss Asahina.

299
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:08,210
Where am I?!

300
00:14:08,210 --> 00:14:09,810
What happened and when
is it right now?!

301
00:14:09,810 --> 00:14:11,000
Umm...

302
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,780
I don't have my TPDD...

303
00:14:16,780 --> 00:14:17,320
Huh?

304
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:17,990
Huh?
It's gone...

305
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:18,850
It's gone...

306
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:25,190
What's wrong?
What's a "TPDD"?

307
00:14:25,190 --> 00:14:27,700
It's classified, but...

308
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:30,800
It's like a time machine.

309
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,800
Why would it
be gone?

310
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,600
I don't know.

311
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:37,830
I should have it,
but I've lost it.

312
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:40,570
Will anyone come
save us?

313
00:14:40,570 --> 00:14:41,840
There's no way...

314
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:44,480
So, what's going
to happen to us?

315
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,280
We're stuck like this.

316
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:50,850
We're going to be left in this time plane,
three years prior,

317
00:14:50,850 --> 00:14:53,320
unable to go back
to our own time!

318
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,290
This is a pretty grave matter.

319
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:56,920
It is!

320
00:14:58,190 --> 00:15:02,100
But for some reason,
I didn't feel any sense of urgency.

321
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:06,570
It was probably the adult Miss Asahina
that took that TPDD-thingy.

322
00:15:06,570 --> 00:15:09,340
That's probably why
she came to the past.

323
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:11,070
As for why, it would
be so that she could

324
00:15:11,070 --> 00:15:13,630
experience losing the TPDD
when she was here.

325
00:15:18,910 --> 00:15:20,850
I think that things are going
to turn out all right.

326
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:22,180
What?

327
00:15:30,690 --> 00:15:33,160
Is this the home of a
Miss Yuki Nagato?

328
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:41,390
I'm not really sure
what to say, but...

329
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:47,800
Will you understand if I say I'm an
acquaintance of Haruhi Suzumiya?

330
00:15:57,990 --> 00:15:58,950
Yo.

331
00:16:00,390 --> 00:16:01,980
Is it all right for us
to come in?

332
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:07,700
And that is who we are
and why we're here.

333
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:11,220
Also, the you three years
from now gave me this.

334
00:16:18,670 --> 00:16:19,870
I understand.

335
00:16:19,870 --> 00:16:23,710
As far as you're concerned, this is
the first time we've met, right?

336
00:16:23,710 --> 00:16:24,510
Yes.

337
00:16:24,510 --> 00:16:27,920
Requesting access to the memory of
the unit in the other time plane.

338
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,720
I have downloaded
the information

339
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,190
from the opposite side of
the linked time boundary.

340
00:16:32,190 --> 00:16:36,020
The me that exists three years from now
and I are the same being.

341
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:40,090
The me three years from now and I
have shared our memories.

342
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:41,130
How?

343
00:16:41,130 --> 00:16:42,230
We synchronized.

344
00:16:42,230 --> 00:16:43,700
I don't understand.

345
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,070
Why are you wearing
a North High uniform?

346
00:16:53,070 --> 00:16:54,640
Are you already enrolled?

347
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:57,340
I am not. The current me
is in standby mode.

348
00:16:57,340 --> 00:16:58,610
Standby?

349
00:16:58,610 --> 00:17:01,320
So you intend to be in standby
for almost three years?

350
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,120
Yes.

351
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:04,920
That sounds like
an awfully long process.

352
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,180
That is my role.

353
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:11,980
There is more than one way
to travel through time.

354
00:17:12,530 --> 00:17:15,700
The TPDD is not the only device
that can control time.

355
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:17,500
It's uncertain and primitive.

356
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:20,270
Umm... What do you mean?

357
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:23,540
The movement of life forms
that use the TPDD

358
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:26,270
is within tolerable ranges,
but it creates noise.

359
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:29,140
To us, it is an
imperfect form.

360
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:32,050
By "us", do you mean
the Thought Entity?

361
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:36,020
Miss Nagato, are you able to travel
through time in a perfect form?

362
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:37,990
The form does not matter.

363
00:17:37,990 --> 00:17:40,780
As long as information can travel
back and forth, it is enough.

364
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:57,100
You don't mean to say that we
should sleep in here, do you?

365
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,040
Yes.

366
00:17:58,040 --> 00:17:59,610
Together, with Miss Asahina?

367
00:17:59,610 --> 00:18:00,600
Yes.

368
00:18:01,510 --> 00:18:02,040
Lie down.

369
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:02,540
Lie down.
Straight to the point!

370
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:03,210
Straight to the point!

371
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:04,410
You'll just be sleeping.

372
00:18:04,410 --> 00:18:07,180
Well, that's my intention,
too, but...

373
00:18:09,180 --> 00:18:11,950
I... I guess we don't have any choice
but to do what we're told...

374
00:18:12,390 --> 00:18:13,580
Yes...

375
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:46,910
What, really?

376
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:49,060
What's the matter?

377
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:51,160
Is that the TPDD?

378
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:54,390
No, this is simply
a radio wave watch.

379
00:18:54,830 --> 00:18:57,100
Thank goodness,
we're back.

380
00:18:57,100 --> 00:19:01,090
It's just after 9:30 PM on the July 7th
that we left from.

381
00:19:04,170 --> 00:19:05,270
How did you do it?

382
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:08,580
I suspended the flow of information
inside of a selected time-space.

383
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:10,480
I then released
the time suspension

384
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,310
at a pre-designated point in
the time-space continuum.

385
00:19:12,310 --> 00:19:14,580
You mean you stopped time?!

386
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:20,040
Miss Nagato stopped time
in this room for three years.

387
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:25,430
And when today came around,
she released the time stop... right?

388
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:26,230
Yes.

389
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:27,990
I can't believe it!

390
00:19:28,460 --> 00:19:29,990
Which means,
in other words...

391
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:34,370
That time when you told me
you were an alien and stuff...

392
00:19:34,370 --> 00:19:37,800
Miss Asahina and I were in
the next room, asleep?

393
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:38,700
Yes.

394
00:19:41,210 --> 00:19:44,440
I always thought that you
were pretty clever,

395
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,250
but you're actually omnipotent,
aren't you?

396
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:47,550
That's not true.

397
00:19:47,550 --> 00:19:49,250
This was a special case.

398
00:19:49,250 --> 00:19:50,780
Emergency mode.

399
00:19:50,780 --> 00:19:54,220
It doesn't happen often.
It has to be something rare.

400
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,090
Thank you.

401
00:19:56,090 --> 00:19:57,320
It was nothing.

402
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,230
Can you read
what this says?

403
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:08,760
"I am here."

404
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:10,600
That's what it says.

405
00:20:13,010 --> 00:20:18,240
Could it be that it's written in
the language of some alien race?

406
00:20:20,650 --> 00:20:22,640
Nagato didn't answer me.

407
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,910
I'm sorry.
Actually, I...

408
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:30,250
I don't really understand.

409
00:20:30,690 --> 00:20:32,360
I'm just an underling...

410
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:34,260
No, not even that.

411
00:20:34,260 --> 00:20:37,400
I mean, I'm more like
a trainee, so...

412
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,400
And yet you're hanging around
with Haruhi.

413
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:45,390
Well, I never thought that
Miss Suzumiya would catch me!

414
00:20:50,010 --> 00:20:53,950
All I do is obey the orders
of my superior...

415
00:20:53,950 --> 00:20:57,550
Maybe I should say the
people above me.

416
00:20:57,550 --> 00:21:02,680
So sometimes I don't understand
the things that I'm doing.

417
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:08,400
I wonder if her superior
is the adult Miss Asahina.

418
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:13,230
The adult Miss Asahina had to know
how things turned out for us.

419
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:17,190
But it looks like she didn't tell
this Miss Asahina any of it.

420
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:22,310
I guess that people from the future
have their own rules and laws.

421
00:21:22,310 --> 00:21:24,280
I'm sure that someone
will tell her.

422
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,340
When everything falls
into place.

423
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:31,650
The next day was,
of course, July eighth.

424
00:21:31,650 --> 00:21:34,420
Consciously I knew that
it was the next day,

425
00:21:34,420 --> 00:21:36,420
but physically, it had been
three years and a day

426
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:38,520
since I had come
to school.

427
00:21:42,860 --> 00:21:45,870
What's wrong? Did you eat a poison
mushroom or something?

428
00:21:45,870 --> 00:21:48,670
Not really. I'm just melancholy
from remembering some stuff.

429
00:21:48,670 --> 00:21:51,760
Memories from
previous Tanabatas.

430
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:54,600
Is that so?

431
00:21:55,910 --> 00:21:57,210
Hey, Nagato.

432
00:21:57,210 --> 00:21:59,680
Miss Asahina really is
from the future, right?

433
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:00,580
Yes.

434
00:22:00,580 --> 00:22:03,650
If that's the case, it feels like
the processes that link

435
00:22:03,650 --> 00:22:06,190
the past and the future
don't quite add up right.

436
00:22:06,190 --> 00:22:07,650
What do you mean?

437
00:22:07,650 --> 00:22:09,290
Previously, Miss
Asahina said that

438
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:11,990
there's no connection between
the past and the future.

439
00:22:11,990 --> 00:22:13,930
But in going back
three years,

440
00:22:13,930 --> 00:22:17,160
I provided Haruhi with knowledge
she didn't need.

441
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:20,100
She ended up coming
to North High,

442
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:23,500
and she started looking for people
who weren't normal...

443
00:22:24,140 --> 00:22:25,730
There's a chance
that's why.

444
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:30,840
There's a definite connection between
the past and the future.

445
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:33,280
This contradicts the explanation
that Miss Asahina gave me.

446
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:39,050
A contradictory set of theories
cannot explain its own contradictions.

447
00:22:39,620 --> 00:22:43,420
Is that supposed to be
an explanation?

448
00:22:43,420 --> 00:22:44,950
You'll eventually understand.

449
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,860
This is what she means.

450
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:56,640
Right now, my king is currently
in check by your rook.

451
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:59,800
"Oh no, what do I do?
Where shall I flee to?"

452
00:23:03,210 --> 00:23:06,980
Now, what was contradictory
about what I just did?

453
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:12,290
In our case, the king really
isn't all that important.

454
00:23:12,290 --> 00:23:15,360
What's important to us
is the queen.

455
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:16,650
I see.

456
00:23:17,090 --> 00:23:19,230
I don't know when something
will happen next,

457
00:23:19,230 --> 00:23:22,660
but when it does, I hope it doesn't
require so much thinking.

458
00:23:22,660 --> 00:23:25,030
I'd prefer that things stay
nice and peaceful.

459
00:23:25,030 --> 00:23:27,360
Would you prefer for
something to happen?

460
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:32,260
Why, you!

461
00:23:43,980 --> 00:23:46,550
Sora kara ochite kitanda
It fell from the sky

462
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:49,290
Subete no negai wo nosete
With all of the wishes
that were made upon it

463
00:23:49,290 --> 00:23:53,890
Hitotsu no hoshi niwa
chotto omokatta kana
Maybe it was a little too heavy
for a single star

464
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:57,160
Yappari nanika henda yo
Something just doesn't
seem right

465
00:23:57,160 --> 00:23:59,800
Kokoro no kimi ga kieta
The image of you in my mind
has vanished

466
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:03,970
Tashika ni oboeteru tte
ieruno kai?
Can I say that I
remember you clearly?

467
00:24:03,970 --> 00:24:05,510
Tomare!
Stop!

468
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:09,280
Kako wa jibun no mono
The past belongs to me

469
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:13,850
Touzen daretomo torikaetakunai
Of course I don't want to trade it
with anyone else

470
00:24:13,850 --> 00:24:15,180
Nazenara
That's because

471
00:24:15,180 --> 00:24:20,450
Basudei datta watashitachi niwa
It was my birthday,
and when we saw each other

472
00:24:20,450 --> 00:24:23,220
Deai ga umareta toki ni
We could see the first dream

473
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:25,690
Hajimete no yume ga mieru
That we had
when we were born

474
00:24:25,690 --> 00:24:30,560
Doushiyouka tte nayanda koto mo
Worrying about "what do I do?"

475
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:34,470
Ima omoeba waraeru hodo
datta yo ne
Is laughable when I
think about it now

476
00:24:34,470 --> 00:24:37,170
Mou wasureteta
I've already forgotten it

477
00:24:37,170 --> 00:24:39,230
Kimi wo sagasou
Let's search for you

